FESI.Interpreter
Class EcmaScriptEvaluateVisitor

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--FESI.Interpreter.EcmaScriptEvaluateVisitor
public class EcmaScriptEvaluateVisitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements EcmaScriptVisitor, EcmaScriptConstants

The evaluate visitor use the visitor pattern to evaluate the parsed code. Use for both main program and functions (using different entries). A new evaluator is used everytime as it contains the return code (because we can return only one variable).

The parse tree must have been preprocessed by the variable and function visitors first.

evaluateWith

public ESValue evaluateWith(ASTStatement node,
                            EvaluationSource es)
                     throws EcmaScriptException
This is a subevaluator. It evaluates a tree which represents a with statement. It is called indirectly via the evaluator when a with statement is encountered in the tree.

node - The parsed tree (annotated for variables)
